{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0bd75df7-2232-4315-81c0-37e57fe3f4ad","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as \"skipped\" (not failed) in test results, with your reason message visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"297b62b1-6ee5-45a8-9a69-8cdc8376a3a4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. Let me provide a concise answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":217,"requestId":"4810:2AD648:7875E6:8ABEA7:69FBE703"},"id":"09202af9-1a1c-4969-a10e-67c8503bc015","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:12:40.587Z","parentId":"c8f11a04-ac69-428f-a76b-c0c033fb9d12"}
